Get Square of two digit number
Step 1: Take any two digit number to be squared. Step 2: Consider the first digit out of that number and add 0 to it. Step 3: Multiply these number twice. Step 4: Multiply First digit and Second digit with 10. Step 5: Multiply answer of Step 4 with number 2. Step 6: Take the square of last digit. Step 7: Take the addition of Step 3, Step 5 and Step 6.
Ex: Let’s take the example of 67
Step 1: Take any 67 number to be squared. Step 2: Consider the first digit (6) out of that number and add 0 to it which will become 60. Step 3: Multiply these number twice (60*60) which is 3600. Step 4: Multiply First digit (6) and Second digit(7) with 10, (6*7*10)which is 420. Step 5: Multiply answer of Step 4(420) with number 2, (420*2) which is 840. Step 6: Take the square of last digit(2) which is 49. Step 7: Take the addition of Step 3(3600), Step 5(840) and Step 6(49).
3600 + 840 + 49 4489
